# 📄 PPT to PDF Converter (Python + comtypes) – Windows Only

This project allows you to convert `.pptx` (PowerPoint) files into `.pdf` format using Python, **without corrupting the original content**. It uses only libraries installable via `pip`, fulfilling all task constraints.

## ✅ Project Requirements
- 🔁 Convert `.pptx` to `.pdf` using Python
- 🔐 Ensure files are **not corrupted** during conversion
- 📦 Use only libraries installable with `pip` (no system tools like `brew`)
- 📄 Maintain a `requirements.txt` for all dependencies

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Tool               | Purpose                              |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Python 3.x         | Programming Language                 |
| comtypes (via pip) | Windows COM interface for PowerPoint |
| Microsoft PowerPoint | Required for backend automation     |

---

## 📥 Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/ppt-to-pdf-converter.git
   cd ppt-to-pdf-converter
Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
-----

## Project structure

ppt-to-pdf-converter/
├── convert.py           # Main conversion script
├── requirements.txt     # Dependencies (pip-installable)
├── sample.pptx          # (Optional) Demo input file
├── output.pdf           # Output generated after script runs
└── README.md            # Project documentation


